<LP>
   GREENWICH, Conn. -- Publicker Industries Inc., an
industrial chemicals and textile maker, said it purchased a
group of nine companies -- five manufacturers, three service
concerns and a distribution business -- from Hanson
Industries Inc., the U.S. unit of Hanson PLC of Britain, for
$31.7 million.
   Publicker had agreed to buy 10 companies from Hanson
Industries for $36 million; the sale of the 10th concern is
expected to be completed in January.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the year ended Sept. 30, the nine-company group had
revenue of $69.3 million and operating profit, before
corporate charges and one-time items, of $5.1 million.
</TEXT>
